{"id":"decision-proxy-container-name","type":"decision","fact":"The proxy container is identified by a fixed Docker name (easy-proxy), queried via 'docker ps -f name=^easy-proxy$'. Docker is the single source of truth - no state file.","recommendation":"Address the container by name (EASY_PROXY_NAME) in proxy.sh. Do not reintroduce a state file to track the container id.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"human","reference":"Architectural decision - issue #5","date":"2026-05-18"}],"tags":["architecture","docker","proxy"],"affectedFiles":["commands/proxy.sh"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-05-18T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-05-18T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"decision-bats-test-gate","type":"decision","fact":"The pre-push and task-completion gate runs 'bats test/' (fast pass/fail). kcov coverage is informational only - instrumenting bats with kcov takes 7+ minutes, too slow to gate.","recommendation":"Keep enforcement.command in .coverage-thresholds.json as 'bats test/'. Run 'kcov coverage bats test/' manually for a coverage report; never wire kcov into CI or hooks.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"discovered building the test harness, issue #7","date":"2026-05-18"}],"tags":["testing","coverage","kcov","bats","ci"],"affectedFiles":[".coverage-thresholds.json",".husky/pre-push"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-05-18T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-05-18T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
